descript.abstract: U.S. and Canada Highways represents the major highways of the United States and Canada. These include interstates and inter-metropolitan area highways and major roads.
descript.purpose: U.S. and Canada Highways provides a subset of highways and roads for national, state, and provincial display.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:100,000.

enttyp.enttypd: The lines represent the major highways of the United States and Canada.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.
Prefix directions of the address attributes for the features.

attr.attrdef: Prefix type is a standard Esri address component used for prefix types. It is a result of address standardization.

attrdomv.udom: Prefix street types of the address attributes for the features.

attr.attrdef: The name of the highway. Where a highway segment has more than one name, the higher-level name will be used, and always in this order: interstates, then U.S. highways and then state highways.
The suffix street type. A street designator or type refers to the portion of a road name that is called "ST," "AVE," "PL," etc.

attrdomv.udom: Suffix street types of the address attributes for the features.
Suffix directions of the address attributes for the features.

attr.attrdef: The shield represents the name based on its Primary Highway Name.

edom.edomvd: Interstate - Business Loop or Business Route
U.S. Highway - Business Loop or Business Route
State Highway - Business Loop or Business Route

attr.attrdef: The HWY_NUM field indicates the number that appears in the shield for that highway. This will be present only for interstates, U.S. highways, state highways, the Trans-Canada Highway, provincial highways, and Autoroutes. The HWY_NUM field is populated only on FCC segments of A1*, A2* and A3*.
The length of the highway segment in miles.

citeinfo.title: TomTom StreetMap Premium for ArcGIS - North America v. 11.1

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Extracted the data set from TomTom StreetMap Premium for ArcGIS v. 11.1. Exported the data set to a shapefile. Renamed local state highway section from '30' to '210', near Redlands, CA. Added the MILES attribute and calculated its values. Converted the data set to SDC. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.

dataqual.logic: The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using tools in ArcGIS. The SDC data set is then imported into a file geodatabase to verify, validate, and if needed repair the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

horizpa.horizpar: The positional accuracy matches or is better than the positional accuracy of the Census TIGER/Line® coordinates. The positional accuracy of the TIGER/Line coordinates at best is +/- 167 feet.
